The Senator representing Kogi West Senatorial District in the National Assembly, Dino Melaye, has reacted to report that he promised to give disqualified Big Brother Naija housemate, Tacha 30 million Naira. Reports had on a Saturday emerged that the lawmaker made the pledge after Tacha’s disqualification yesterday on his Twitter handle. DAILY POST recalls that Big Brother disqualified Tacha on Friday over act of provocation and violence. Biggie, who quoted an article from the Big Brother’s rules, said ”You are guilty of physical assault and violence.” He, therefore, disqualified Tacha from the reality show and issued two strikes to Mercy.  But speaking on his alleged pledge, Dino Melaye said the report was ‘fake. Alongside a picture of the alleged promise he wrote, “This is a fake account. Not from me.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.